LINK END--><br>Which results in a swiftclaw sash.<br><br>Lesser guard of haste is a shoulder piece:6% haste<br>Greater guard of haste also shoulder:11% haste<br>Sporali gloves:10% haste<br>swiftclaw sash:15% haste. <br><br>I'm leaning torwards the swiftclaw sash, because I can solo it.  Although I want to go on a raid, and my guild is encouraging mid/low level raids, if you want the item, then you organize it.  Since the swiftclaw sash is a soloable quest, that is much easier, besides it being a better item.<br><br>Your thought, or any other items I should consider?  I have 50pp to my name, so don't say 'buy one.'  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Kegulik, 26 troll. &lt;Sunrunners&gt; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uapollonike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apollonike</A> at: 6/4/02 10:00:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ucayenoms.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CayenOMS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 10:09:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> I have found the swiftclaw sash fairly reasonable to attain.  You just can't beat the haste for the time/or money involved.  Besides, on random inspects, people pass over it, thinking its a FBSS.  Makes you look a tad more...I dunno...expensive : )<br><br><br>Cayen/Jondolar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/utorvald.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torvald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FF0000><CENTER>Beast Lord</FONT></CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 10:12:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> I don't know about the Gloves, but from personal experience the Sash and Guards are a pain.<br><br>The Sash, not only are the heretics a rare random spawn, bring a tracker or forget it, but the Sash is the rare reward for the turn in. It took 6 hours to see our first heretic, we never saw a second.<br><br>For the Guards. I am not sure how have the spawn rate worked for the named Elementals. We cleared the isle many times, only saw one named spawn and it dropped a spiny weapon. I know I shopped for a Guard for a while and never found anyone who had ever seen one on 7th Hammer.<br><br>My recommendation is hunt for or buy a FBSS, and someday if you should happen to find one of the above be nice and pass it to one of your twinks..)<br><br>Azmod, 55 Beastlord, 7th Hammer<br>Torvald, 51 Shaman, 7th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ucayenoms.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CayenOMS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 10:19:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> The biggest advantage I see to the swiftclaw sash is simply this:  for many levels, it is a very nice hunting locale (depending on race, but even Iksars can take advantage of SB).  It doesn't seem like too much of a chore when you are hunting there normally, and chance upon a heretic....better yet, group with a ranger or druid, to keep an eye out.  Concentrating on the act of finishing the quest will make it seem that much longer.<br><br>If I remember right, I leveled my shaman there from 30 to 39 in roughly 2 weeks...casual play. Solo. Drinking the entire time.<br><br>Cayen/Jondolar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uapollonike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apollonike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/4/02 10:27:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> Cayen-I looked at the sash a bit mor after I posted this, and noticed it's a few zones from painell, and that's the only way in.  Is a troll beastlord worshipping innoruk kos in painell?  <br><br>And if not, how do I get there?  I'm thinking the odus scion is the only way to go.  Any other ways?<br><br>Thanks in advance.<br><br>Kegulik, 26 troll-4 tortured levels until sow. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uapollonike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apollonike</A> at: 6/4/02 10:27:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uthrogo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Throgo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/5/02 12:18:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> I'd rather farm the guards in highpass keep for cash and buy an FBSS, or get 1.5-2.5k more for some SCHW gloves(i think) the 10ac w/ stats 22% gloves.  Save your cash people!  As beastlords we are one damn effective cash farming class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uapollonike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apollonike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/5/02 1:05:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> What level do you have to be to farm the guards?  <br><br>Another thought just occured to me<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> o you have to have velious to access stonebrunt mountains?  I hope not, because I don't have it<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Still exploring my options, but I'm leaning torwards the sash, because the zone is good xp soloing, whereas I'd have to organize a raid AND get lucky for the other items.  The sash, I only have to get lucky<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Kegulik, 26 troll.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ucayenoms.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CayenOMS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/5/02 6:20:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> You can pretty much avoid Paineel;  you will however have to go through the Warrens.  Best bet here is to grab an invis and follow someone through that knows the way. I think it involves passing by one Erudite necro/sk guard, but its been so long I can hardly remember.  I know that several of my friends, and even my wife's Iksar made it through to SB with no prob.<br><br>And also, its part of the old world...dont sweat it, no Velious needed : )<br><br>Cayen/Jondolar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usqrlcub.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SqrlCub</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FF0000><CENTER>Beast Lord</FONT></CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/5/02 6:25:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> Paineel isn't a problem going through as a troll worshipping Inny. The only guards that you have to worry about are at the entrance but they are relatively low level so you can easily flash of light them and get through. When I fought there for a little I bound in shadow haven and just ran through to fight in the warrens. Unfortunately it wasn't worth my time then. Maybe I will go back later and get off KOS. I never went to stoneburnt with my troll but would think it would be similar as going to the warrens.<br><br>Poop <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ucoyoteharts.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyo