rd.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Kegulik, 27 troll. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uredgiki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>redgiki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FF0000><CENTER>Beast Lord</FONT></CENTER></span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/5/02 8:04:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> Stonebrunt is pretty easy to get to, but a bit time-consuming your first time through, particularly if you don't have a map.  Level range on critters in the zone ranges from level 12 mobs on the low side, to level 32-33 mobs on the high side.  A really good mid-level zone, generally low population because, well, there's only one way in, one way out, the loots not that good, and XP has only a small multiplier.<br><br>Take the Odus Scion to get to the Toxxulia Forest wizard spire.  You will zone in facing SOUTH at this spire.  Head south until you hit the zone wall, turn right, and you will soon see the entrance to Paineel.<br><br>Once in Paineel, follow the left wall around.  If you are level 20+, chances are you won't get aggro from anything that can kill you.  There are two skeletons who will not aggro you if you run past them through the middle, and one Erudite guy that *may* aggro you, but casts lame level 1 necro spells so you can outrun him easily.  No need to flash of light.<br><br>Follow the right wall around once you are in the greenway, and you'll reach a tunnel.  Follow that, take your first left, welcome to The Warrens.<br><br>Now here you need a map.  Get a good one, figure out where you are going, and get to Stonebrunt.  Pet pathing here is awful, so be prepared to need him and have him be running around somewhere else.  Voila, you are there.<br><br>Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ucassicdestron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassic Destron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Primal Ooze</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 4:07:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> Enjoying 7th Hammer Torvald? :p <p><br><table><tr><td><img src="http://www.lordoftherings.net/images/ca_obloo.jpg" alt="Legolas"></td><td><p><b>Legolas Greenleaf</b></p><p>If I were a character in <A HREF="http://lordoftherings.net/" TARGET="_"><I>The Lord of the Rings</I></A>, I would be Legolas, Elf, a son of the King of Mirkwood.</p><br>~Cassic Destron~<br>60th Assassin of The Nameless<br>Proud Memeber of <A HREF=http://www.the-first-seal.co.uk/>The First Seal</A></table><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/udharlfarstrider.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dharl Farstrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 5:26:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1771.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mid/low haste items</span><hr size=1> You might also want to look into the haste belt that drops in Hollowshade Moor as part of the War.  It drops off a named grimling after the grims take over the owlbear cave.  The belt is AC10 with some decent stats and clocked around 11 percent has